      "content": "### Why Highground Even Matters\n\nHighground wins fights. You control the angle, you see more, and you’re harder to hit. If you can consistently retake highground, you’ll dominate more endgames, win more 1v1s, and make smarter plays overall.\n\n**Retakes you should learn first**\n- Ramp + Floor + Wall into 90s\n   - The classic. Quick triple build into tight 90s. Spam this to gain elevation fast while staying protected.\n   - Use this when you’ve got space and want to punish someone who’s pushing too high.\n\n- Mini-Ramp Retake\n    - Throw a floor under you mid-ramp, then ramp again. Fast and efficient.\n  - It’s low-risk, perfect when you’re low on mats or need quick vertical movement.\n\n- Cone Flip Retake\n   - Drop a cone over your opponent’s ramp, place a floor, then ramp over it.\n  - This surprises them and gives you height while staying covered.\n\n- Double Ramp + Wall Surf\n   - Throw two ramps (one on each side) and wall as you move up — lets you climb safely and quickly.\n   - Use this when the opponent’s building aggressively or box-peeking.\n\n- Mix-ups & Freestyles\n   - Combine cones, walls, and edits. Don’t be predictable. Switch it up with side jumps, fake-outs, and delayed ramps to throw your opponent off.",
