      "content": "### How to Actually Get Good at It\n- Warm-Up Routine:\n  - Pick one retake and drill it 5–10 times in creative. Get your fingers used to the motion.\n  - Then link 2–3 retakes in a row and build that rhythm.\n- Edit Speed = Confidence:\n  - Pre-edit, confirm fast, and don’t second guess. Fast walls + cone edits are your bread and butter in fights.\n- Peace Control As You Retake:\n  - After you gain height, immediately place walls/cones around them so they can’t escape. That’s your kill window.\n- React to Their Moves:\n  - If they try to overbuild, flip a cone or ramp over their head. If they turtle, box them with cones and edit down.\n- Don’t Waste Mats:\n  - Only do full 90s when you need to. Sometimes a simple ramp and cone retake is enough. Save mats for the actual fight.\n_ _",
