      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "### Combat Mindset\n- Every retake should lead to pressure. You’re not just building, you’re setting up your next shot. Always think:\n  - “How do I trap them?”\n  - “Where’s my angle?”\n  - “Can I end this fight now?”\nUse height as a weapon, not a flex.\n\n**Training Plan**\n1.    Solo Creative – Pick one retake and grind it 10x until it’s clean\n2.    Chain Two Retakes – Combine them mid-fight\n3.    Fight Real Players – Queue up and test it under pressure\n4.    Watch VODs – Record your fights, see which retakes work or fail\n\n- You need to learn these 4–5 retakes and drill them till they’re muscle memory. Start with the basic 90s and cone flip. Then mix in double ramps and mini-ramp combos. Edit fast, build smart, and don’t waste mats. Every retake is a setup for pressure and a kill. If you get this down, you’ll win way more fights and be way more confident in build battles.",
